Document: GridMap
Path: godot/classes/class_gridmap.rst
Summary: This section details the properties of the GridMap node, including settings for navigation baking, cell positioning, sizing, collision behavior, and assigned resources.

Properties:

bake_navigation (bool): If true, this GridMap creates a navigation region for each cell that uses a MeshLibrary item with a navigation mesh. The created navigation region will use the navigation layers bitmask assigned to the MeshLibrary's item. Default: false.
Method: set_bake_navigation(value: bool)
Method: is_baking_navigation()

cell_center_x (bool): If true, grid items are centered on the X axis. Default: true.
Method: set_center_x(value: bool)
Method: get_center_x()

cell_center_y (bool): If true, grid items are centered on the Y axis. Default: true.
Method: set_center_y(value: bool)
Method: get_center_y()

cell_center_z (bool): If true, grid items are centered on the Z axis. Default: true.
Method: set_center_z(value: bool)
Method: get_center_z()

cell_octant_size (int): The size of each octant measured in number of cells. This applies to all three axis. Default: 8.
Method: set_octant_size(value: int)
Method: get_octant_size()

cell_scale (float): The scale of the cell items. This does not affect the size of the grid cells themselves, only the items in them. This can be used to make cell items overlap their neighbors. Default: 1.0.
Method: set_cell_scale(value: float)
Method: get_cell_scale()

cell_size (Vector3): The dimensions of the grid's cells. This does not affect the size of the meshes. See cell_scale. Default: Vector3(2, 2, 2).
Method: set_cell_size(value: Vector3)
Method: get_cell_size()

collision_layer (int): The physics layers this GridMap is in. GridMaps act as static bodies, meaning they aren't affected by gravity or other forces. They only affect other physics bodies that collide with them. Default: 1.
Method: set_collision_layer(value: int)
Method: get_collision_layer()

collision_mask (int): The physics layers this GridMap detects collisions in. See Collision layers and masks in the documentation for more information. Default: 1.
Method: set_collision_mask(value: int)
Method: get_collision_mask()

collision_priority (float): The priority used to solve colliding when occurring penetration. The higher the priority is, the lower the penetration into the object will be. This can for example be used to prevent the player from breaking through the boundaries of a level. Default: 1.0.
Method: set_collision_priority(value: float)
Method: get_collision_priority()

collision_visibility_mode (DebugVisibilityMode): Show or hide the GridMap's collision shapes. If set to DEBUG_VISIBILITY_MODE_DEFAULT, this depends on the show collision debug settings. Default: 0.
Method: set_collision_visibility_mode(value: DebugVisibilityMode)
Method: get_collision_visibility_mode()

mesh_library (MeshLibrary): The assigned MeshLibrary.
Method: set_mesh_library(value: MeshLibrary)
Method: get_mesh_library()

physics_material (PhysicsMaterial): Overrides the default friction and bounce physics properties for the whole GridMap.
Method: set_physics_material(value: PhysicsMaterial)
Method: get_physics_material()
